1 packet haloumi/grill cheese
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 capsicum
½ tin sweetcorn
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet BBQ Mayo
1 packet sour cream
1 bunch coriander
drizzle Olive Oil

Pat dry haloumi and cut into thick slices.
Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat.
Cook haloumi until golden brown, 2 mins each side.
Transfer to a plate.

Meanwhile, roughly chop capsicum and drain corn (1/2 tin for 2P / 1 tin for 4P).
Return pan to high heat with oil Cook veggies, tossing, until softened and lightly charred, 3-4 mins. Add spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 min.

Microwave rice until steaming, 2-3 mins.
Add rice and spinach to the pan and toss with veggies. Season to taste.
Plate up rice.
Top with haloumi, veggies, BBQ mayo and sour cream Tear over coriander.